---
import PageLayout from "@layouts/PageLayout.astro"
import Container from "@components/Container.astro"

const pageTitle = "About"
const pageDescription = "The story, convictions, and discipleship vision behind Canon & Compass."
---

<PageLayout title={pageTitle} description={pageDescription}>
  <section class="bg-white dark:bg-black py-24 text-ink dark:text-white">
    <Container size="md">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl">
        <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-zinc-500 dark:text-zinc-400">Our story</p>
        <h1 class="mt-4 text-3xl md:text-4xl font-serif font-bold tracking-tight">About Canon & Compass</h1>
        <p class="mt-6 text-base md:text-lg text-zinc-700 dark:text-zinc-300">
          Most people feel something is off—but struggle to name what, or why.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-4 text-base text-zinc-700 dark:text-zinc-300">
          Canon & Compass exists to help believers regain bearings in a loud age: to trace what we’re carrying back to what’s forming us, and to re-root in the reality of Scripture. We believe discipleship should be both <em>beautiful</em> and <em>concrete</em>—not abstract theology or behavior management, but whole-life formation grounded in God’s world.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-4 text-base text-zinc-700 dark:text-zinc-300">
          This project began from a simple desire: to pair theological depth with everyday clarity. To offer a map for people navigating tension, exhaustion, and uncertainty—not with shallow fixes, but with a way of seeing that reshapes how we walk through the world.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-4 text-base text-zinc-700 dark:text-zinc-300">
          Every essay, pathway, and practice here is built around a core conviction: <strong>Faithfulness is not formulaic. But it is possible—when rooted in truth.</strong>
        </p>
      </div>
    </Container>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-stone-50 dark:bg-zinc-900 py-20 text-ink dark:text-white">
    <Container size="md">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl">
        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-serif font-bold tracking-tight">How this space is arranged</h2>
        <p class="mt-4 text-base text-zinc-700 dark:text-zinc-300">
          Canon & Compass isn’t a single track. It’s a set of places designed to meet you where you are—whether you need grounding, diagnosis, or a path forward.
        </p>

        <ol class="mt-8 space-y-6 text-base text-zinc-700 dark:text-zinc-300">
          <li class="flex gap-4">
            <span class="flex h-8 w-8 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-black text-white dark:bg-white dark:text-black font-semibold">1</span>
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink dark:text-white">The Clearing</h3>
              <p class="mt-1">
                A place to slow down, regain orientation, and learn to see again—without fixing, defending, or deciding yet.
              </p>
            </div>
          </li>

          <li class="flex gap-4">
            <span class="flex h-8 w-8 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-black text-white dark:bg-white dark:text-black font-semibold">2</span>
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink dark:text-white">The Forests</h3>
              <p class="mt-1">
                Worldview diagnosis: naming the climates—cultural, philosophical, and spiritual—that quietly shape what feels normal (including large-scale false gospels).
              </p>
            </div>
          </li>

          <li class="flex gap-4">
            <span class="flex h-8 w-8 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-black text-white dark:bg-white dark:text-black font-semibold">3</span>
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink dark:text-white">Fruit Paths</h3>
              <p class="mt-1">
                Personal formation paths that begin with what’s showing up in your life, trace it to its roots, and lead you toward truth that forms different fruit over time.
              </p>
            </div>
          </li>

          <li class="flex gap-4">
            <span class="flex h-8 w-8 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-black text-white dark:bg-white dark:text-black font-semibold">4</span>
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink dark:text-white">Foundations</h3>
              <p class="mt-1">
                Depth for the long work: Canon Notes, Compass Points, and Pillars that help truth take root slowly and hold under pressure.
              </p>
            </div>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </div>
    </Container>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-white dark:bg-black py-20 text-ink dark:text-white">
    <Container size="md">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl space-y-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-serif font-bold tracking-tight">What anchors our work</h2>
        <ul class="space-y-4 text-base text-zinc-700 dark:text-zinc-300">
          <li><strong class="text-ink dark:text-white">Scripture first:</strong> We are committed to orthodox, historic Christianity. Every path submits to the canon.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-ink dark:text-white">Whole-person formation:</strong> True change touches our imagination, intellect, relationships, and habits. We design resources that invite all of you.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-ink dark:text-white">Presence in the present age:</strong> We engage modern questions without panic, trusting that Christ is Lord over every cultural moment.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-ink dark:text-white">Hopeful realism:</strong> Naming pain and confusion honestly is not cynicism; it is the first step toward redemption.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-base text-zinc-700 dark:text-zinc-300">
          Canon & Compass is written and curated by Zach for readers who want something deeper than spiritual shallowness, cultural drift, or reactionary answers. The aim is not to build a personality around the work, but to offer a faithful, formation-oriented map.
        </p>
      </div>
    </Container>
  </section>

  {/* SECTION 4 REPLACED */}
  <section class="bg-stone-50 dark:bg-zinc-900 py-20 text-ink dark:text-white">
    <Container size="md">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl space-y-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-serif font-bold tracking-tight">Who this is for</h2>
        <p class="text-base text-zinc-700 dark:text-zinc-300">
          Canon & Compass is for those who want clarity without simplification, and hope without control.
        </p>

        <ul class="space-y-4 text-base text-zinc-700 dark:text-zinc-300">
          <li>
            <strong class="text-ink dark:text-white">If you’re spiritually tired of noise,</strong> and want to rediscover quiet faithfulness without spectacle or panic.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong class="text-ink dark:text-white">If you’re intellectually awake but not formed,</strong> and you’re ready for truth to shape instincts—not just opinions.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong class="text-ink dark:text-white">If you’re discipling others,</strong> and you want something sturdier than tips: a way to name what’s happening and walk it out over time.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <p class="text-base text-zinc-700 dark:text-zinc-300">
          You don’t need to have the right words to begin. You only need the honesty to start where you are.
        </p>
      </div>
    </Container>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-white dark:bg-black py-20 text-ink dark:text-white">
    <Container size="md">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl space-y-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-serif font-bold tracking-tight">Doctrinal posture</h2>
        <p class="text-base text-zinc-700 dark:text-zinc-300">
          Canon & Compass is a Christian discipleship project shaped by Scripture and guided by the pattern of life, truth, prayer, and spiritual formation seen in the New Testament Church. It is not aligned with a single denomination, and it does not aim to foreground denominational identity. Its theological instincts are closest to a charismatic expression of Christian faith, while seeking to remain anchored first in Scripture.
        </p>
        <p class="text-base text-zinc-700 dark:text-zinc-300">
          Its role is narrower than a church or formal teaching ministry: to offer biblical reflection, spiritual diagnosis, and formation-oriented guidance for readers who want to see their lives more clearly under the lordship of Christ.
        </p>
        <p class="text-base text-zinc-700 dark:text-zinc-300">
          Where Canon & Compass makes arguments, it does so with conviction but not with claims of infallibility. It seeks to distinguish between central Christian truths, which bind the conscience of the Church, and secondary judgments, where faithful believers may share the same Lord and Scriptures while differing in emphasis, language, or conclusion.
        </p>
      </div>
    </Container>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-stone-50 dark:bg-zinc-900 py-20 text-ink dark:text-white">
    <Container size="md">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl space-y-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-serif font-bold tracking-tight">Contact and feedback</h2>
        <p class="text-base text-zinc-700 dark:text-zinc-300">
          Questions, corrections, or thoughtful feedback can be sent to <a href="mailto:contact@canonandcompass.com" class="underline underline-offset-4 decoration-black/30 dark:decoration-white/30 hover:decoration-current">contact@canonandcompass.com</a>.
        </p>
        <p class="text-base text-zinc-700 dark:text-zinc-300">
          Every message is read with care, but response times may vary and not every note will receive a personal reply.
        </p>
      </div>
    </Container>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-stone-50 dark:bg-zinc-900 py-20 text-ink dark:text-white">
    <Container size="md">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl space-y-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-serif font-bold tracking-tight">What this site is and is not</h2>
        <ul class="space-y-4 text-base text-zinc-700 dark:text-zinc-300">
          <li><strong class="text-ink dark:text-white">This is a discipleship resource:</strong> It is written to help readers slow down, examine roots, and pursue greater clarity, repentance, and faithfulness under Scripture.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-ink dark:text-white">This is not a substitute for embodied care:</strong> Canon & Compass does not replace life in a faithful local church, pastoral shepherding, licensed counseling, psychiatric care, or emergency support.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-ink dark:text-white">This is not a crisis resource:</strong> If you are in danger, in acute distress, or unable to function safely, seek immediate in-person help from local emergency services or a qualified clinician.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-ink dark:text-white">This is an independent solo writing project:</strong> It should be read as accountable Christian reflection, not as an official statement from a church, denomination, or formal ministry institution.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </Container>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-white dark:bg-black py-20 text-ink dark:text-white">
    <Container size="md">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl text-center space-y-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-serif font-bold tracking-tight">Where to begin</h2>
        <p class="text-base text-zinc-700 dark:text-zinc-300">
          Start where you are. If you need grounding, enter The Clearing. If you want to name the climate shaping you, explore The Forests. If a specific pattern has become clear, walk a Fruit Path.
        </p>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-3">
          <a href="/the-clearing" class="rounded-full border border-black/15 dark:border-white/20 px-4 py-2 text-sm font-semibold hover:bg-black/5 dark:hover:bg-white/15 transition-colors duration-200 ease-in-out">Enter The Clearing</a>
          <a href="/forests" class="rounded-full border border-black/15 dark:border-white/20 px-4 py-2 text-sm font-semibold hover:bg-black/5 dark:hover:bg-white/15 transition-colors duration-200 ease-in-out">Explore The Forests</a>
          <a href="/fruit-path" class="rounded-full border border-black/15 dark:border-white/20 px-4 py-2 text-sm font-semibold hover:bg-black/5 dark:hover:bg-white/15 transition-colors duration-200 ease-in-out">Walk Fruit Paths</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </Container>
  </section>
</PageLayout>
